Selling so-called conversion therapy services to minors remains legal in most U.S. states, but new legislation threatens any federal funding going to the practice.
Rep. Sean Patrick Maloney of New York, co-chair of the growing Congressional LGBT Equality Caucus, filed legislation last month to crack down on any use of Medicaid funds for "conversion therapy."
“Conversion practices are discredited, harmful and not therapy,” Maloney said.
“Until we can just ban conversion ‘therapy’ all together, we must ensure taxpayer dollars aren’t funding a fraudulent practice that has been roundly discredited by the medical community.
"The Trevor Project hears from youth harmed by the dangerous and discredited practice of conversion therapy every week.